  "title": "FLOOR TILER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare tile beds using concrete, plaster, mastic, cement, glue, or mortar, applying tools such as screeds, brushes, and trowels to ensure a solid and level foundation.</li>\n  <li>Align and level tiles using straightedges, spirit levels, and squares to ensure precise patterns and a clean finish.</li>\n  <li>Cut and shape tiles accurately to fit around obstacles and into tight or irregular spaces, utilizing both hand and power tools.</li>\n  <li>Cut, install, polish, and finish granite and marble surfaces, maintaining high precision during installation for long-lasting and professional results.</li>\n  <li>Prepare surfaces for tiling by cleaning thoroughly and applying waterproofing materials or lath as required.</li>\n  <li>Design and install decorative wall and floor mosaics in areas such as kitchens, bathrooms, and living rooms.</li>\n  <li>Carefully tap tiles into place using appropriate tools to ensure proper adhesion while preventing breakage or damage.</li>\n  <li>Read and follow blueprints accurately; measure and mark surfaces to determine the layout and approach for each tiling job.</li>\n</ul>",
